In force from 2024-12-17
Fiat account and Conversion Service
1.  What terms and definitions we use?
As used in these Terms, including the preamble hereof, unless expressly otherwise stated or evident in the context, capitalized terms and expressions shall have the meanings as stipulated under this chapter General and Wallet.
2.  How to add Fiat funds to your Account?
2.1. You have two methods to add Fiat funds to your Account:
2.1.1. using the Service of Instant Deposit; and/or
2.1.2. making a transfer from an account opened in your name with a credit or financial institution. The institution must be registered or have its place of businessin a contracting state of the European Economic Area. Subsequent transfers maybe made from a different account provided it is also opened in your name, or by using the Service of Instant Deposit.
2.2. Should you use the Service of Instant Deposit as your initial method of funding your Account, the following restrictions will apply till you have utilised the method outlined in clause 2.1.2:
2.2.1. you will be limited to using the Conversion Services for up to 1000 euros every 30 days, irrespective of the amount of funds you transfer to your Account or have accumulated therein. This restriction applies to the cumulative value of purchases and sales of crypto assets, calculated at the time of the transactions. The 30-day period commences with the first transaction of the Conversion Service;
2.2.2. you will not be able to use any other services provided by Change (i.e. to withdraw or deposit Cryptocurrency, Stake Cryptocurrency, or trade with CFDs); and
2.2.3. you will not be able to withdraw any Fiat funds.
2.3. Even if you choose the method outlined in clause 2.1.2 as your initial payment, you understand and accept that the payment processing may take some time. During this processing period, or if the payment is processed immediately, we reserve the right to enforce the restrictions outlined in clauses 2.2.1-2.2.3 above for a reasonable period following the payment.
2.4. You acknowledge that all of Fiat funds described in these Terms must belong to you, and that all accounts, as well as credit and debit cards used for the Service of Instant Deposit, must be registered in your name.
2.5. We reserve the right to decline accepting Fiat transfers to your account from any account due to any reason or decline transferring funds to an account that wasnot used to make a transfer in accordance with clause 2.1.2 by notifying you there of. We have also reserved the right to decline accepting any payments while using the Service of Instant Deposit, e.g. to prevent fraud or in case more than 3 different cards have been used.
2.6. In case we decline accepting a Fiat transfer, the funds will be immediately returned to your account opened in a credit institution in accordance with the law. However, if you have only used the Service of Instant Deposit, we reserve the right to retain the funds until the completion of the process outlined in clause 2.1.2 above.
2.7. Irrespective of the method you utilize to fund your Account, all fees and limits as stated in the chapter Fees and Limits will apply.
3.  How to withdraw Fiat funds from your Account?
3.1. You are entitled at all times to instruct us to withdraw any Fiat funds from your Account by instructing us to transfer them to an account you previously transferred funds from as described in clause 2.1.2.
3.2.	We reserve the right to decline to perform a withdrawal, if the withdrawal amount is lower than 10 euros.
3.3. In the case of Account closing you must instruct us to transfer all of the Fiat funds to an account you previously transferred funds from as described in clause 2.1.2 and we will transfer it to your account in accordance with the law.
3.4. However, as stated in section 2 above, if you have used only the Service of Instant Deposit to add funds to you Account, we may decline to fulfill your instruction to withdraw until the completion of the process outlined in clause 2.1.2 above. The same applies if your Account is closed by us in accordance with the chapter General and Wallet
4.  How to buy cryptocurrency?
4.1. In order to buy a supported cryptocurrency with the Conversion Rate in exchange for a specified Fiat currency in accordance with these Terms, you must have had transferred the Fiat funds required for the transaction, as shown to you in the Apps or Website, to our account in accordance with clause 2.1.
4.2.	In order to buy a supported cryptocurrency in exchange for another supported cryptocurrency in accordance with these Terms you must have had transferred to us the equivalent amount of supported cryptocurrency, which is to be used in exchange for the requested supported cryptocurrency and will be automatically debited from your Wallet.
4.3.	In order to buy a supported cryptocurrency with the Conversion Rate in exchange for a specified Fiat currency or supported cryptocurrency, but not having transferred the required amount of the specified Fiat currency or supported cryptocurrency to us, the required specified Fiat currency or supported cryptocurrency must be held at your account or Wallet during the time of buying the supported cryptocurrency as a result of using the Conversion Service.
4.4.	In case you have requested to buy a supported cryptocurrency, the amount of supported cryptocurrency bought by you will be transferred to your Wallet after the completion of the relevant transaction.
5.  How to sell cryptocurrency?
5.1. In order to sell a supported cryptocurrency with the Conversion Rate in exchange for a specified Fiat currency in accordance with these Terms, you must have had transferred to us the equivalent amount of supported cryptocurrency, which is to be used in exchange for the requested Fiat currency and will be automatically debited from your Wallet.
5.2.	In case you have requested to sell a supported cryptocurrency in exchange for a specified Fiat currency, the amount of specified Fiat currency will be transferred to your Account after the completion of the relevant transaction specified in your instruction.
6.  How to buy or sell Investment Gold?
6.1. When buying or selling Investment Gold you have acknowledged and agreed with the third-party and cryptocurrency-related risks, and agreed with the relevant PAX Gold Terms and Conditions and any other relevant terms and conditions of Paxos. We shall not assume any liability for any unavailability of redeeming Investment Gold or the existence or termination of PAXG due to reasons not dependent on us, e.g. dependent on the specifics of the Ethereum blockchain or the issuer of PAXG, including but not limited to the sustainability, insolvency, liquidation or bankruptcy of Paxos or any of the service providers or persons connected to the Investment Gold in general.
6.2.	After every resettlement cycle we ensure that the total amount of Investment Gold we hold on behalf of you with our partners, e.g. Payward Inc., matches with the total amount of Investment Gold held on your Account.
6.3.	In order to redeem your Investment Gold into a specific gold bar, held in an London Bullion Market Association-approved security carrier vault, you must pay us exactly 430 PAXG tokens, as well as the Creation & Destruction Fee, and submit a redemption order through the Apps or via email. Please be advised that you are not able to redeem your Investment Gold into Unallocated Gold. If successful, you will receive a confirmation letter through the Apps or via email, confirming the date and time as of which you must collect and accept the delivery of your gold bar in person from our registered address within 2 weeks. For the delivery of the gold bar you are required to verify your identity by providing your valid passport.
6.4.	You may demand for delivery of a substitute thing from us within 2 years as of the date of the delivery, if the gold bar delivered to you does not conform to the contract, e.g. the gold bar does not have the agreed characteristics, does not possess the quality usual for investment gold or is anyway damaged, provided the gold bar has not been removed from its original package and the damage did not occur after the delivery.
7. How are the transactions carried out?
7.1.  We carry out the transactions described in these Terms on the basis of irrevocable instructions from you, which can be submitted through the Apps or Website.
7.2.  You are not allowed to cancel, reverse, or change any transaction marked as complete after the submission of an instruction in accordance with these Terms. We may unilaterally decline to carry out the transaction by notifying you thereof on the Website and/or in the Apps, and return you the relevant instruments, and shall assume no liability for any damages which arise to you as a result thereof. You may only cancel a pending instruction, if you have submitted it by using the services of Limit Order or Stop Order, provided the Rate Reference you set has not been reached and the transaction has not yet marked as complete.
7.3.  You are displayed all supported cryptocurrencies with the estimated Conversion Rate prior to submitting the instructions in accordance with these Terms and/or exact Conversion Rate for transaction(s) marked as complete. By submitting the instructions in accordance with these Terms you irrevocably confirm to carry out the transaction without certainty of the Conversion Rate.
7.4.  After receiving the instructions in accordance with these Terms, we will complete the requested transaction within 5 business days after receiving the payment (whereas a business day is considered to be a day when banks are open for business in Estonia), unless we decline to carry out the transaction in accordance with clause 6.2. We reserve the right to delay any transaction without notifying you thereof, should we perceive a risk of fraud or illegal activity.
7.5. Considering that the prices of cryptocurrencies and Investment Gold are dependent on fluctuations in the financial market, which we have no control over and which may occur within the withdrawal period, in accordance with Law of Obligations Act § 53(4)(1’) you are not entitled to use the right of withdrawal, including in the case of a distance contract.
8.  What are the technical guidelines and regulations that must be adhered to when utilising our Conversion, Wallet and Staking?
8.1.  You are strictly prohibited from attempting to reverse engineer our trading platform or any of the services provided or circumvent any security measures implemented.
8.2. You are not allowed to employ any software, artificial intelligence, ultra-high speed trading strategies, or mass data entry techniques that could manipulate, exploit, abuse, or provide an unfair advantage when using our systems or services.
8.3. It is not permissible to engage in trades that manipulate our systems or services, this includes manipulation of service fees and hedging.
8.4. It is strictly forbidden to act in an unfair, abusive, manipulative, or illegal manner when utilizing our services. This includes engaging in scalping or any other form of unethical trading practices.
8.5. Engaging in trades or other services with the intention of exploiting price errors is not permitted.
8.6. Engaging in trades or other services with the intention of exploiting system bugs or errors is not permitted. If such circumstance is detected in the course of trading or the use of other services, you are obliged to notify immediately about the issue bugbounty@changeinvest.com.
8.7. Your orders must comply with the rules and regulations of the exchange. Your orders must not be intended to defraud or manipulate the market.
8.8. If you generate profits by violating any of the above rules or your activity results in damage for xChange AS, we reserve the right to withhold assets on your account and we may deduct the amount from your account balances unilaterally, in case of which, we will provide full overview of the circumstances under which the activity takes place. Should assets be withdrawn from your account prior to the detection of any violation, you hereby consent to immediately reimburse all damages resulting from your activities upon receipt of the claim. Additionally, you agree to bear the costs associated with legal fees or similar expenses incurred in pursuing legal action if you fail to comply or refuse to cooperate in resolving the aforementioned claim.
8.9. Any breaches of the aforementioned rules will be documented. We may cancel your orders, freeze, block, and/or terminate our services, your account, and/or our agreement with you in response to such breaches. While we may provide notice in accordance with applicable laws, it is not mandatory for us to do so.
