In force from 2024-12-17
Staking
This chapter sets the terms and conditions for using Staking - cryptocurrency services, which allows you to earn rewards on the supported cryptocurrencies held on your Account. By using the Conversion Service and buying the supported cryptocurrencies as described below, you have agreed to the use of and the terms and conditions of the services. Please be advised that the Staking service described in this chapter is not addressed to and may not be used by Users, who are located in or nationals or residents of specific territories, where such a service is not allowed, including any Restricted Jurisdiction.
1. How Staking works?
1.1.	While using Staking you have to use the Conversion Service, whereby you buy the supported cryptocurrencies, which are shown to you in the Apps, from us, in exchange for specified Fiat currencies or other supported cryptocurrencies, and vice versa. You are entitled to at all times buy specified Fiat currencies or other supported cryptocurrencies from us, in exchange for the supported cryptocurrencies, however in these instances you may not be eligible for the reward.
1.2.	After having bought the supported cryptocurrencies, with Staking all your supported cryptocurrencies may be deposited on your behalf to our Kraken Account, including for the use of services such as On-Chain Staking Services and/or Off-chain Staking Program, operated by third-party custodian, i.e. Payward Trading Ltd and/or BitGo, Inc. and/or our Ledger Vault, whereby access is provided to third-party service "non-custodial validation-as-a-service" providers that facilitate the management of staking processes without taking custody of the cryptocurrencies.
1.3. Interest for the specific calendar day (T) is calculated on a daily basis on the outstanding balance of the supported cryptocurrencies held on your Account at the beginning of the next calendar day (00:00 UTC; T+1), and rewarded shortly after but not later than the end of the day in the same supported cryptocurrency. The expected as well as the exact size and rate of the Staking reward at a specific time is shown to you in the Apps, which in turn is also subject to Staking in accordance with these terms and conditions. For absolute clarity, you are not entitled for a reward for the supported cryptocurrencies or any parts of it at a specific day (T), which were not held on your Account at the moment of the calculation (T+1), including whenever you have submitted a Stop Order or a Limit Order with the supported cryptocurrency.
1.4. For protocols with activation and deactivation periods, we reserve the right to pass rewards on to Users accounts at our discretion. This means for certain cryptocurrencies, the first reward is not distributed the next day, instead being subject to the activation period specified in the App after which regular reward distribution as stated in clause 1.3 will start. This also means that for days prior to the activation period no rewards are earned by the user.
1.5. All fees, including network fees for the aforementioned transfers, have already been deducted from the interest offered.
2. What are the risks?
2.1. Since Staking is in its entirety cryptocurrency services, your supported cryptocurrencies are not subject to statutory or voluntary deposit guarantee schemes or deposit insurance.
2.2. By using Staking you acknowledge that various types of risks are involved, including but not limited to risks relating to the changes in the operating rules or other features, e.g. the existence, availability, sustainability of or forks in the specific protocol or blockchain, or the fluctuation of the value or the existence of any supported cryptocurrencies, including where relevant the fiat currency it is pegged to, counterparty risks, including but not limited to the sustainability, insolvency, liquidation and bankruptcy of one of our partners and their partners, regulatory risks and uncertainties. Should any of the risks realise, you hereby understand and consent that you are solely liable for the consequences, and we shall not assume any liability nor obligations thereof.
2.3. By using Staking you understand and agree that rewarding you with the interest is in our sole discretion, not an obligation, and it is not a guarantee that you will receive the reward as a whole or any parts of it, or by the due date. We have reserved the right to from time to time change the interest rate, which is shown to you in the Apps, and these terms, and temporarily or permanently terminate or discontinue providing the service of Staking at any time, without giving you a prior notice thereof. Should we temporarily or permanently terminate or discontinue the Staking service, you will no longer be eligible for any rewards. Interest calculation will cease as of that calendar day, and we will not be obligated to provide any Staking rewards for the calendar day on which the service was terminated or discontinued.
2.4. Please be advised that Staking, especially the Off-chain Staking Program, is not addressed to and may not be used by Users, who are not treated as Eligible participants, including are located in or nationals or residents of: (i) any Restricted Location; (ii) Australia, Canada, Denmark, Finland, France, Germany, Hong Kong, Italy, Japan, Luxembourg, the Netherlands, Singapore, Sweden, the United Arab Emirates, the United Kingdom or the United States; (iii) any jurisdiction where the Off-chain Staking Program is not legally authorized; or (iv) any jurisdiction where the use of the Off-chain Staking Program would be illegal or otherwise violate any applicable laws or regulations of that jurisdiction.
2.5. In addition to agreeing to these terms, when using Staking you also consent and agree to abide by the terms of our partners. Please also pay extra attention to the risk disclosure sections. Relevant documents are available at
https://www.bitgo.com/legal/terms-of-use/
,  and
https://www.kraken.com/legal
.
3. How is the security of the supported cryptocurrencies ensured?
3.1.	Change has performed and is constantly re-performing relevant due diligence on its partners and the financial, reputational and regulatory risks surrounding them. If it becomes known or Change deems the counterparty risk, including any security risk to your supported cryptocurrencies, to be unacceptable, we will immediately terminate the partnership and/or the service, and inform you thereof in the Apps.
3.2. In terms of Staking, despite cryptocurrency exchanges not qualifying for deposit insurance programs, because exchanges are not savings institutions, your cryptocurrencies deposited on Kraken Account are subject to a semi-annual advanced cryptographic accounting procedure conducted by trusted and independent third-party auditors, so-called Proof of Reserves audits, to ensure that the balance of the supported cryptocurrencies is backed by real assets.
